Sure, let's simplify it further:

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Determination to Succeed</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            background-color: #f4f4f4;
            color: #333;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
        }
        header {
            background-color: #4CAF50;
            color: white;
            text-align: center;
            padding: 1em 0;
        }
        .container {
            max-width: 800px;
            margin: 2em auto;
            padding: 1em;
            background-color: white;
            box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
        }
        .post {
            margin-bottom: 2em;
            padding: 1em;
            border-bottom: 1px solid #ddd;
        }
        .post h2 {
            margin-top: 0;
        }
        .footer {
            text-align: center;
            padding: 1em 0;
            background-color: #333;
            color: white;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <header>
        <h1>Determination to Succeed</h1>
    </header>
    <div class="container">
        <div class="post">
            <h2>Welcome to Determination to Succeed</h2>
            <p>This blog is dedicated to sharing insights, experiences, and tips on how to stay determined and achieve success in various aspects of life. Stay tuned for more posts!</p>
        </div>
        <div class="post">
            <h2>First Post</h2>
            <p>Welcome to my first blog post! Here, I'll share my journey and the lessons I've learned along the way. Remember, determination is the key to success.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
    <footer class="footer">
        <p>&copy; 2024 Determination to Succeed. All rights reserved.</p>
    </footer>
</body>
</html>
```

This is a simplified version with just the essentials: a header, a container for blog posts, and a footer. Let me know if this works for you or if there are any other changes you'd like!
